# Change scope

## Structural changes

- Do not add a new module under `src/lib/` without updating [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) (diagram, module table, ownership).
- Prefer extending an existing layer over creating catch-all folders (`utils/`, `misc/`, `helpers/`).
- Read [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) before editing module boundaries or data flow.

## Thin boundaries

- **`main.c`**: argument parsing, usage, mapping errors to exit codes — no business logic.
- **`app/`**: orchestration and viewer state — delegate parsing to `io/`, rendering to `ui/`, movement to `nav/`.
- Extract testable logic into `nav/`, `cmd/`, `layout/`, or `io/` rather than testing ncurses directly.

## User-facing sync

- CLI flag or exit code change → `man/csvi.1` and `docs/architecture.md`.
- Key binding or `:` command change → [Commands.md](Commands.md).

## General

- Minimize diff scope — do not refactor unrelated code in the same change.
- Match existing naming, error handling, and file layout in the surrounding module.
